---

---

<section
  id="get-started"
  class="border-t border-db-border bg-db-surface px-6 py-20"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[640px]">
    <p class="section-label section-label-accent">Setup</p>

    <h2
      class="mb-4 text-[clamp(28px,4vw,40px)] font-semibold leading-tight tracking-tight"
    >
      Add it to your Vite config.<br />That's it.
    </h2>

    <p class="mb-9 leading-7 text-db-muted">
      Design Bridge runs alongside your dev server. The panel appears
      automatically in the browser. No build step changes. No extra config.
    </p>

    <div class="code-block mb-7">
      <div class="code-block-header">
        <span class="code-block-filename">vite.config.ts</span>
      </div>
      <pre
        class="code-pre"><code><span class="text-db-accent">import</span> <span class="text-db-text">&#123; defineConfig &#125;</span> <span class="text-db-accent">from</span> <span class="text-db-green">'vite'</span>
<span class="text-db-accent">import</span> <span class="text-db-text">&#123; designBridge &#125;</span> <span class="text-db-accent">from</span> <span class="text-db-green">'@design-bridge/vite-plugin'</span>

<span class="text-db-accent">export default</span> <span class="text-db-amber">defineConfig</span><span class="text-db-text">(&#123;</span>
  <span class="text-db-text">plugins:</span> <span class="text-db-text">[</span><span class="text-db-amber">designBridge</span><span class="text-db-text">()]</span>
<span class="text-db-text">&#125;)</span></code></pre>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-3 text-sm text-db-muted">
      Run <code
        class="rounded border border-db-border bg-db-surface px-2 py-0.5 text-[13px] text-db-text"
        >vite dev</code
      >
      — the panel appears in your browser. Done.
    </p>
    <p class="text-[12px] text-db-ghost">
      More integrations coming: Next.js, Nuxt, SvelteKit
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
